f $H^0_{\\mathfrak m}(R)$ is large relative to\nthe rest of the module, generalizing the case of Buchsbaum rings.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 5 Oct 2018 05:54:56 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 14 Jan 2020 11:45:44 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-01-15"}
